<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<recipe>
    <name>Thai Beef, Potato and Peanut Curry</name>
    <indexCharacter>T</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Heat coconut milk in a large saucepan 

2. Add beef and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook for 1 hour uncovered 

3. Meanwhile, in a large pot, heat oil. Add curry paste and saute for 5 minutes. 

4. Add coconut-beef mixture, potatoes, onions, fish sauce, tamarind water, and spices. Cook until vegetables are tender- about 15 minutes. 

5. Add peas and peanuts and simmer for 2 minutes longer.</instructions>
